		<description>I went about solving the 404 and 500 issue a while ago and I think the solution was a pretty good one. Unfortunately it never got implemented fully.

Obviously the main idea would be to try to solve stuff automatically, if that doesn&#039;t work use the referrer or the URL to search for suggestions and if no matches are found refer the visitor to the home page, sitemap or something similar. In any case you should send an automatic email to the admin for internal broken links and maybe also for external broken links and links with no referrer. This info should then be used to manually add aliases that are passed into the first step of autosolving...</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I went about solving the 404 and 500 issue a while ago and I think the solution was a pretty good one. Unfortunately it never got implemented fully.</p>
<p>Obviously the main idea would be to try to solve stuff automatically, if that doesn&#8217;t work use the referrer or the URL to search for suggestions and if no matches are found refer the visitor to the home page, sitemap or something similar. In any case you should send an automatic email to the admin for internal broken links and maybe also for external broken links and links with no referrer. This info should then be used to manually add aliases that are passed into the first step of autosolving&#8230;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
